NOTE: In the original FormMapR, cells with missing elevations were generally given values of zero. However, in LITAP, they remain as NA (missing) to more accurately reflect the nature of the measurement.

NOTE: l2div was originally calculated as the distance to the crest using the location of the nearest crest cell as well as the distance to this nearest crest cell. In the C++ version of formMapR this was changed to the distance of the nearest peak cell, which I believe is incorrect. Therefore this R package uses distance to nearest crest cell.
